    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for the foundational points. Could you go a bit deeper into the economic side of it? Specifically, how would someone argue that strict enforcement actually protects the domestic labor market and helps prevent the depression of wages for low-skilled workers? My students need to be able to articulate that connection really clearly if they're going to win the round.",
